🎯 Interview Questions
Why is it called Route 53? Because DNS uses **Port 53**.

Is Route 53 a Load Balancer? No.Route 53 performs DNS resolution.A Load Balancer distributes traffic.

Does Route 53 host websites? No. It only directs traffic.
Applications are hosted on services like
- EC2
- ECS
- EKS
- Elastic Beanstalk
- S3

Can Route 53 work outside AWS? Yes. It can route traffic to applications hosted both inside and outside AWS.

Can Route 53 point to an Application Load Balancer? Yes. This is one of the most common production architectures.

Can Route 53 perform Health Checks? Yes. It continuously monitors applications and automatically routes traffic away from unhealthy endpoints.

💡 Key Takeaways
- Route 53 is AWS's managed DNS service.
- Converts domain names into IP addresses.
- Supports domain registration.
- Supports health checks.
- Supports multiple routing policies.
- Works inside and outside AWS.
- Integrates seamlessly with EC2, ALB, CloudFront, S3, ECS, EKS, API Gateway, and more.
- Improves availability, fault tolerance, and disaster recovery.


